<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Mount Google Drive in CentOS</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            background: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0px 0px 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h2 {
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .step1 { background-color: #ffcccb; }
        .step2 { background-color: #d1c4e9; }
        .step3 { background-color: #c8e6c9; }
        .step4 { background-color: #ffecb3; }
        .reference { background-color: #b3e5fc; }
        pre {
            background: #333;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }
        .pagination {
            margin-top: 20px;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .pagination a {
            text-decoration: none;
            padding: 10px 15px;
            border: 1px solid #007bff;
            border-radius: 5px;
            color: #007bff;
            margin: 5px;
            display: inline-block;
        }
        .pagination a:hover {
            background: #007bff;
            color: white;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="step1">Step 1: Download and Unzip Rclone</h2>
        <pre>
curl -O https://downloads.rclone.org/rclone-current-linux-amd64.zip
unzip rclone-current-linux-amd64.zip
cd rclone-*-linux-amd64
        </pre>

        <h2 class="step2">Step 2: Copy Binary File</h2>
        <pre>
sudo cp rclone /usr/bin/
sudo chown root:root /usr/bin/rclone
sudo chmod 755 /usr/bin/rclone
        </pre>

        <h2 class="step3">Step 3: Install Manpage</h2>
        <pre>
sudo mkdir -p /usr/local/share/man/man1
sudo cp rclone.1 /usr/local/share/man/man1/
sudo mandb
        </pre>

        <h2 class="step4">Step 4: Configure Rclone</h2>
        <pre>
rclone config
n) New remote
name> remote
12 (Google Drive)
1 (Full access)
n (Edit advanced config)
y (Use auto config?)
n (Team drive)
y (Confirm configuration)
        </pre>

        <h2 class="reference">Reference Command</h2>
        <pre>
rclone ls driveku:
        </pre>

        <div class="pagination">
            <a href="#">&#9665; Previous</a>
            <a href="#">Next &#9655;</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

